    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A group of these objects owns collectively one T-instance, allowing access to stored instance from parallel threads; if one object updates its T-instance, then it makes a copy of T-instance first and become the only object in new group </para>
    </detaileddescription>
